default My expertise is not with regard to the numbers of primates held privately, but rather with the fundamental issues of the adequacy of the protection of primate welfare 
defaultfor pet primates 
defaultand the appropriateness of the keeping 
defaultof primates as “pets”. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAs a result of my 
default39 years of 
defaultexperience with non-human primate biology, behaviour and conservation
default both in the wild and captivity
default, I can perceive no ethical, husbandry, conservation or historical justifications for continuing to 
defaultallow the keeping of primates as companion animals in the UK.
